cs.IT, cs.NE, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.EM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the capacity analysis of the hybrid channel and sub-channels, which is a key topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a neural communication mode as one of the components of the HNC system and discusses the design of the neural to molecular interface. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the design of relay interfaces between different modes of nano communications, which is related to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the transmission of data in different modes of nano communications, which can be considered as a multimedia application. 
5. cs.EM (Electromagnetism): The paper discusses the use of terahertz communication as one of the components of the HNC system, which is related to electromagnetism.
